==English==

===Adjective===
'''constant'''
# [[unchanged|Unchanged]] through [[time]] or [[space]]; [[permanent]].
# [[consistently|Consistently]] recurring over time; persistent
# [[steady|Steady]] in purpose, action, feeling, etc.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[pysyvä]] (1), [[muuttumaton]] (1), [[vakio-]] (2, ''in compounds'')
*French: constant {{m}}, [[constante]] {{f}}
*German: [[konstant]]
*Italian: [[costante]] {{m}} & {{f}}
*Swedish: [[konstant]]
*Ukrainian: [[сталий]] {{m}} (st'''a'''lyj)

===Noun===
'''constant'''
# That which is [[permanent]] or [[invariable]].
# {{algebra}} A [[quantity]] that remains at a fixed value throughout a given discussion.
# {{science}} Any property of an experiment, determined numerically, that does not change under given circumstances.
# {{computing}} A variable that is assigned a static value.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[vakio]]
*French: constante {{f}}
*German: [[Konstante]] {{f}}
*Italian: [[costante]] {{f}}
*Swedish: [[konstant]] {{c}}
*Ukrainian: [[сталина]] {{f}} (stalyn'''a''')

===Related terms===
